&gt; Catalytic centre

The active centre of the ribozyme is composed of four layers of base triples.(PDB ID: 7EZ0)<br />

The transition state of first step catalysis.MB binds to the 3â€™-hydroxyl group of the exogenous guanosine in the first step, functioning as a general base to activate the nucleophile. Another Mg2+ (MA) stabilizes the 3â€™-leaving group, acting as a general acid. These two metal ions exchange their roles in the second step reaction, of which MA functions as the general base and MB as the general acid.<br />

